snippet.textDisplay:
A perfect example of a show ending when they ran out of ideas is Corner Gas, and the creator, Brent Butt, actually said in interviews (when asked why he didn’t want to make more episodes) that he didn’t want to keep going if there was nothing new to say. And then they released a movie (amazing experience in theatres, and was the only time I’ve sung the Canadian national anthem in the theatre) which was decent, but more impressively is the cartoon continuation that (I think?) is still going today! You can tell the different medium allows them to do things they never could’ve done with a live action show, so it feels completely fresh while still being true to the original show.
The original show is only 6 seasons but I strongly suggest people watch it, especially if they’re from Canada and/or a small town it is an amazing show that will always hold a special place in my heart

snippet.textDisplay: Although it's valid to point out The Walking Dead's severe drop in popularity, I haven't found it going on too long as i'm a reader of the graphic novel it is based on and should just about bring the show to a 12th and final season in april 2022. It's two most recent seasons: 9 & 10 - with it's revamp of writer's - has, for me at least, propelled the show into a state where it IS in its endgame and has drastically gotten better after seasons 7 and 8 were, both, handled and received extremely poorly (100% valid, as these seasons were lacklustre to say even the least) I just thought people should know from a person that knows where the show is headed that YES it will end very soon, as set in motion by the events of the graphic novels.

snippet.textDisplay: ‘Star Wars: The Clone Wars’ was originally supposed to only have 3 seasons, but because of all its Emmy nominations and wins, it got renewed up to season 7. Right after season 4 aired, Disney bought Star Wars. So they made Season 5 (which they were already working on), but it didn’t have a complete ending. So in a last ditch effort, in early 2014, they released a 6th season on Netflix. With a 7th being cancelled right after season 6. Originally the 6th season was supposed to be 26 episodes, but got cut into 13. And now, on February 21st, 2020, the show will get an, admittedly short, 7th season. Something that will finally wrap it up. This was kind of a hodgepodge of all the topics you gave us to answer. But yeah.

snippet.textDisplay: I always thought that Once Upon a Time ended badly because the last season made no sense. They could have just finish the show at the season 6 finale and that would have been fine. But then again they probably got renewed by producers and the writers probably had no clue on what to write about. I think that introducing a whole new story line in the last season of the show was a pretty weird choice because that just left the audience confused and wondering. We had no closure, sure the curse was broken but that's just a spin off of the entire first season. They also decided to add new characters and take out all of the major ones like Emma, Hook (OG Hook not the dream one), Snow, Prince Charming etc. And even the new characters felt like they didn't belong. I still really like the show but I would have just appreciated if I had some closure.

Avatar is the perfect example of a show staying no longer than it needs to, and it really is perhaps my all time favorite.

Also, despite being only 26 episodes, Cowboy Bebop has a very satisfying conclusion. Of course I'd want more episodes in that amazingly realized world--same with Avatar--but they wrap themselves up in such a way that makes me respect the creators and enjoy the show that much more.

Burn Notice is too long.

snippet.textDisplay: Honestly, the one show that went on for WAY too long was Glee. Now, I know that Glee wasn't like the greatest show, but it honestly should've ended after season 3 because the following seasons were an absolute mess and unbearable to watch.  They introduced a ton a new characters no one wanted or cared about and they made everyone else into an absolute dickhead.
